title: J'den Cox on rivals, wrestling, and mental health
description:
The 2019 freestyle wrestling world champion is partially deaf and suffered from depression but has found a way to thrive. Speaking before the protests in the USA, J'den talks candidly about Tokyo 2020 postponement, mental health, and his rivalry with team-mate Kyle Snyder.

For more go to olympicchannel.com/podcast
